Security in and around Jos Prison, Plateau State Police Command and Headquarters of the State Security Service (SSS) in Jos was on Sunday tightened up following rumors of planned jail break by armed group. As early as 8.am on Sunday morning major roads within Jos metropolis were taken over by well-armed Policemen loaded in Police trucks. All roads leading to Police headquarters, Jos Prison were blocked thereby causing heavy traffic with Church worshippers trapped in the traffic gridlock for hours. The Plateau State Police Command in a statement in Jos on Sunday over the development,stated that Plateau State especially Jos is very peaceful. According to the statement, “The Command has adopted a new security strategy in line with it’s normal routine patrol and check. “Also, the Command wants to be proactive in any intelligent report at our disposal as it is our core mandate to protect lives and property” the statement stressed.. The Command urged everyone to go about their legitimate business in Jos metropolice without fear.